📚 Re-Interpretation Engine (RIE) v1.0

How to reread works and surface deeper meaning without drifting into projection

⸻

🧭 Core Principle

Every text has layers: surface wording, structural intent, and historical context. Re-reading lets you triangulate them—not recover a single “true” meaning.

There isn’t one hidden answer.

There are:
	•	bounded interpretations that survive evidence + context

⸻

🧠 Why rereading feels more powerful

When you revisit a text:
	•	you’ve changed
	•	your mental models are richer
	•	you notice patterns you couldn’t before

So it feels like:

“I see what they really meant now”

More precisely:

You’re mapping the text onto a higher-resolution internal model

⸻

🔍 How to actually do it (method)

1. Literal pass
	•	What is explicitly said?

⸻

2. Structural pass
	•	What problem is the author solving?
	•	What assumptions are baked in?

⸻

3. Constraint pass
	•	What couldn’t they say directly?
	•	What context (political, social, business) shaped the writing?

⸻

4. Translation pass
	•	Rewrite the idea in modern language
	•	Strip style → keep structure

⸻

5. Test pass (critical)
	•	Does this interpretation:
	•	match other parts of the text?
	•	match known outcomes / reality?
	•	hold under contradiction?

If not:

it’s projection, not extraction

